job_details.full_text:
Fullstack (Laravel en Vue) developer

Wil jij deel uitmaken van een revolutie in softwareontwikkeling? Bij SevenLab geloven we in de kracht van AI om de toekomst vorm te geven. Met onze unieke Software Development As A Service methode nemen we alle frustraties van traditionele softwareontwikkeling weg en realiseren we cutting edge (gen)AI toepassingen.

* Ontwikkelen van schaalbare en krachtige (AI) applicaties met behulp van het Laravel/Vue-framework
     * Samenwerken met ons team van ongeveer 15 collega's aan end-to-end AI-applicatieontwikkeling
     * Incidenteel gebruik van low-code platforms zoals n8n en Flutterflow i.c.m. Je fullcode ervaring en skills
     * Vertalen van complexe AI-concepten naar praktische toepassingen voor onze klanten
     * Bijdragen aan het continu verbeteren van onze Software Development As A Service methode

profile_classification.rationale: The job description focuses heavily on traditional full-stack development using Laravel and Vue.js, with AI mentioned primarily as a domain or application area rather than a core technical requirement for the role itself. While it mentions 'cutting edge (gen)AI applications' and 'translating complex AI concepts', the core responsibilities and technologies listed (Laravel, Vue.js, n8n, Flutterflow) point towards a software development role that *utilizes* AI, rather than one that *develops* or *engineers* AI models or systems. There is no mention of core AI/ML tasks like model training, fine-tuning, data engineering for ML, or specific AI/ML frameworks. Therefore, it does not fit the criteria for ML Engineer or GenAI Engineer and is best classified as Ambiguous.

The mention of 'incidenteel gebruik van low-code platforms zoals n8n en Flutterflow i.c.m. Je fullcode ervaring en skills' points to using development tools, including low-code, alongside traditional coding.
